  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db1\u0ddd \u0db1\u0d82\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0da7\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cabinet approval to raise casino",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet approval has been granted to streamline the casino industry in this country.",
        "The Casino Business (Regulation) Act No. 17 of 2010 and the Betting and Gaming Tax Act No. 40 of 1988 provide for the regulation of the casino industry in Sri Lanka, and under Act No. 17 of 2010, licenses must be issued to operate casino businesses in Sri Lanka.",
        "The proposal submitted by the Prime Minister to the Cabinet of Ministers in this regard shows that due to the fact that the necessary orders to enforce the provisions of the said Act have not been issued so far, no license has been issued to any casino business under the said Act, so it is difficult to formally collect taxes from the institutions currently engaged in the casino business.",
        "Therefore, to issue orders under the Casino Business (Regulation) Act No. 17 of 2010 and to introduce the necessary amendments to the Betting and Gaming Tax Act No. 40 of 1988 for the purpose of regulating such businesses and collecting taxes due to the Government in due course, Finance, Economic As the Minister of Stabilization and National Policy, Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe has presented this proposal."
      ],
